    <h1>How to Choose a Strong Research Topic</h1>

    <p class="positioning-text">
      1. Start with a broad area of interest and list possible ideas.<br>
      2. Check what research already exists to avoid repetition.<br>
      3. Narrow your topic to something practical and researchable.<br>
      4. Ensure your topic has clear academic and real-world value.<br>
      5. Confirm your topic can be completed within your timeframe and resources.
    </p>

    <p class="positioning-text">
      Use this structured approach to move from vague ideas to a focused research question that is academically meaningful.
    </p>
